race.comment: SUPER SUNNY (3) presents third-up off a 1.6L defeat in stronger at Belmont. He led in that over the 1200m and is likely to take a sit over the longer sprint. Strips fitter and is all set to find winning form. ROYALZEL (1) was tracking well before being outgraded at Belmont Park. The speed-bred gelding is going to be much more competitive today, and the 3kg claim brings him right into it. WESTERN IMPACT (4) is hard to catch but has pieces of form that would have him in the finish. Has the 2kg claim and the extra metres suit his racing style. LUCKY HEART (8) was safely held resuming last start over 1400m at Bunbury. Maps well and Louis replaces the apprentice. Better suited and will be fitter.  Consider.
